Commentary Text: Shivam Mavi to du Plessis, out Caught by Venkatesh Iyer!! Nope, he won't get the orange cap. Ruturaj can chill. Okay, now onto more important things, Faf's played an absolute blinder here. But he holes out, swinging at a pretty full delivery on off to try and smoke over long-on, but just doesn't quite get under the length, dragging it off the inside-half to the fielder by the boundary. 192 .. du Plessis c Venkatesh Iyer b Shivam Mavi 86(59) [4s-7 6s-3]

That was a flatter delivery and Uthappa missed the reverse to be hit in front of the sticks. That looked adjacent but the pair decided to review. Three Reds have taken away the only review that CSK had. But what an important innings from Uthappa as he was on the offensive from ball one. Commentary Text: Narine to Ruturaj Gaikwad, out Caught by Shivam Mavi!! And the break has applied the brakes for CSK. Commentary Text: Chahar to Shubman Gill, out Lbw!! Deepak Chahar is not even turning back at umpire Richard Illingworth in his celebrappeal. That is absolutely plumb in front. Full marks to MSD for bringing back Chahar to complete his overs. Chahar bowls a dipping slower ball low full toss, Gill was across the line to access the fine leg region, misses and is hit low in front of off stump. From 91/0, it's 108/4. KKR's big match inexperience at the top order showing. CSK showing their big match experience by just not panicking despite a good start for the opponents. Now onto the very experienced Morgan and DK. Shubman Gill lbw b Chahar 51(43) [4s-6]
